## Company Overview

World Labs, legally known as World Labs, is a private company headquartered in San Francisco, California, United States. The company operates in the fields of spatial intelligence, AI research, and product development. World Labs positions itself as a leading spatial intelligence company, focusing on building frontier world models capable of perceiving, generating, reasoning, and interacting with the 3D world. The company is also involved in AI research and product development.

## Business Model and GTM

World Labs is a product company that develops advanced AI models and tools. Its flagship product, Marble, is a generative 3D world model that allows users to create spatially cohesive, high-fidelity, and persistent 3D worlds from a single image, video, or text prompt. The company states that its products enable creators and developers to explore the next frontier of AI through spatial, world-model-driven experiences.

## Funding & Investor Profile

World Labs has raised a total of $230,000,000 USD. Details regarding specific investors or funding rounds are not disclosed.

## Growth Momentum

World Labs has released several products, including Marble and a research preview of RTFM, a generative world model that generates video in real-time. The company has also shared progress toward creating persistent, navigable 3D worlds that can be explored in a browser. These product releases indicate a focus on innovation and expanding the capabilities of AI in spatial intelligence.

## Visibility & Market Sentiment

Not disclosed.

## Risks and Challenges

Not disclosed.

## Outlook

The company states that it is exploring the next frontier of AI with its spatial, world-model-driven experiences. This focus on cutting-edge technology and product development suggests a positive outlook for continued innovation and potential market leadership in the spatial intelligence sector.
